Two people can be married in their backyard by their great uncle if they want to be.  It depends on your interpretation of marriage.  If two people are sentimental enough, they could perform a very serious rite in which they declare each other eternally belonging to the other.  The reason it's not often done is because society's perception of marriage is doing it with the legal bind that comes along with it.<br>
